  <main class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Key Research Questions</h1>
      <p class="sub">
        Scientific questions that guide modelling, inversion, and experimental validation for curved composite wind-turbine blades.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <div class="panel-head">
        <h2>Research focus</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          The project targets reliable thermographic reconstruction and inversion on curved, anisotropic, layered structures under realistic inspection constraints.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>RQ1: Curvature and anisotropy</h3>
          <p>How do curvature and fibre-driven anisotropy reshape eddy-current distribution and transient heat diffusion, and how can models capture this efficiently?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>RQ2: Fibre-direction representation</h3>
          <p>How can fibre directions be represented consistently on a curved surface (tangent-plane mapping or curvilinear coordinates) for conductivity and thermal tensors?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>RQ3: Inversion and reconstruction</h3>
          <p>Which reconstruction/inversion strategies remain stable under noise, lift-off variation, and limited access, while providing interpretable defect indicators?</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <div class="panel-head">
        <h2>How we address them</h2>
        <p class="muted">A structured mapping from questions to methods and validation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Modelling</h3>
          <p>Multi-physics simulation with geometry parameterisation, coil excitation design, and anisotropic tensor definitions aligned with fibre directions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Algorithms</h3>
          <p>Thermographic feature extraction and model-informed inversion designed for curved composite structures.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Validation</h3>
          <p>Controlled samples and experimental benchmarking to quantify sensitivity, robustness, and repeatability.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <div class="panel-head">
